<raw><![CDATA[    Investing.com â€“ The pound extended losses against the U.S. dollar on Wednesday, hitting a 7-day low amid mounting fears over euro zone sovereign debt and ahead of a key interest rate decision by the Federal Reserve.GBP/USD hit 1.5207 during early European trade, its lowest since April 19; the pair subsequently consolidated around 1.5224, shedding 0.27%.Cable was likely to find short-term support at 1.5191, the low of April 19, and resistance at 1.5523, the high of April 15.On Tuesday, Standard & Poor's cut Greece and Portugal's credit ratings, saying it was concerned about Greece's ability to carry out reforms needed to tackle its gaping budget deficit and Portugal's ability to deal with its debt load. The move sparked a flight to safety on concerns that the euro zone's debt problems were spreading.Sterling also slipped against the euro on Wednesday, with EUR/GBP gaining 0.45% to reach 0.867.Later Wednesday, the U.S. Federal Reserve was set to announce a key interest rate decision and release a statement from its Federal Open Market Committee, which traders were likely to scrutinize for clues to future shifts in monetary policy.             ]]></raw>
